works.description: The space age officially began 50 years ago when Russian cosmonaut Yuri Gagarin became the first human to journey into the outer space when his Vostok spacecraft completed an orbit of the Earth on April 12, 1961. The whole world is celebrating the big event. Considering the fact that this is a big occasion for space enthusiasts and after a Russian businessman spent $3 million to buy the Vostok 3KA-2 capsule yesterday, we are expecting next month’s Bonhams’ Space History Sale to start a bidding war
